  "prompt": "How should mild rotatory scoliosis be treated once it is detected?",
  "response": "When mild rotatory scoliosis is detected, treatment typically involves the following approaches:\n\n1. Initial Monitoring\n- Regular follow-up appointments to track curve progression\n- X-ray evaluations at specific intervals\n- Monitoring spine curvature during growth periods\n\n2. Conservative Treatment Options\n- Physical therapy\n- Specific scoliosis-focused exercises\n- Stretching and strengthening programs\n- Posture improvement techniques\n\n3. Bracing\n- Recommended for children/adolescents with curves 25-40 degrees\n- Custom-fitted orthopedic braces\n- Worn during growth periods to prevent curve progression\n\n4. Lifestyle Modifications\n- Maintaining healthy weight\n- Regular physical activity\n- Ergonomic adjustments\n- Proper sleeping and sitting postures\n\n5. Additional Considerations\n- Age of patient\n- Skeletal maturity\n- Rate of curve progression\n- Overall spinal alignment\n\n6. Surgical Intervention\n- Typically reserved for severe cases\n- Curves progressing beyond 45-50 degrees\n- Significant functional impairment\n\n7. Complementary Approaches\n- Chiropractic care\n- Specialized massage\n- Potential alternative therapies\n\nConsultation with a spine specialist is crucial for personalized treatment planning.",
